1
00:00:01,355 --> 00:00:06,525
Theme of home is something
that’s of universal application.

2
00:00:06,655 --> 00:00:09,485
It’s a common saying
or understanding

3
00:00:09,485 --> 00:00:14,375
that everyone 
is searching for their home.

4
00:00:14,618 --> 00:00:18,578
We even have one book published
called ‘Home Comfort’.

5
00:00:18,811 --> 00:00:22,481
[Age of Search for Reality the Beautiful]

6
00:00:22,804 --> 00:00:27,244
But home … 
you can say ‘home’ implies

7
00:00:27,604 --> 00:00:36,764
family, loving affectionate
relationships.

8
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:42,440
But for that to be something 
real and substantial,

9
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:49,139
and not stereotypical,
then it‘ll have to begin

10
00:00:49,139 --> 00:00:56,909
with first establishing
our own identity.

11
00:00:58,459 --> 00:01:01,829
The perennial questions: 
“Who am I?

12
00:01:01,829 --> 00:01:05,629
Where’ve I come from? 
What is my purpose?”

13
00:01:06,049 --> 00:01:10,639
So, when you think about search,
like, this is the age of search.

14
00:01:10,639 --> 00:01:13,109
We have Google.

15
00:01:13,109 --> 00:01:19,569
Search—this whole age 
is predominated by search.

16
00:01:19,588 --> 00:01:21,928
Social networking—
people are searching.

17
00:01:21,928 --> 00:01:24,088
They’re searching
for their counterparts.

18
00:01:24,088 --> 00:01:27,408
We’re searching … 
What are we searching for?

19
00:01:27,418 --> 00:01:35,478
Besides the objective things 
like how to acquire

20
00:01:35,478 --> 00:01:39,448
consumer items at good prices.

21
00:01:39,448 --> 00:01:44,998
That’s one idea. 
That’s good idea.

22
00:01:44,998 --> 00:01:48,047
But what are we really 
searching for?

23
00:01:48,047 --> 00:01:51,037
What’s driving us to consume?

24
00:01:51,037 --> 00:01:57,525
What’s driving consumption
is the search for fulfillment.

25
00:01:58,525 --> 00:02:00,635
So, how will we find 
fulfillment,

26
00:02:00,635 --> 00:02:05,485
if in fact 
we are the subjective aspect—

27
00:02:05,485 --> 00:02:09,735
conscious living beings, 
embodied,

28
00:02:09,735 --> 00:02:14,864
navigating the objective existence.
Subjects navigating the objective world.

29
00:02:15,184 --> 00:02:20,884
We have mistakenly bought
into the notion

30
00:02:20,884 --> 00:02:25,984
that through the acquisition …

31
00:02:25,984 --> 00:02:29,084
to acquire, control and consume …

32
00:02:29,084 --> 00:02:34,204
Through acquisition and consumption
that we’ll find fulfillment.

33
00:02:34,214 --> 00:02:37,794
But that means 
for the soul, subject,

34
00:02:37,794 --> 00:02:44,039
to try and acquire, 
control and consume objects—
 

35
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:47,619
it’s not to address 
its base necessity.

36
00:02:47,619 --> 00:02:56,149
What is the soul is searching for
is sweetness, love, affection.

37
00:02:56,149 --> 00:02:59,498
Sometimes it mistakenly
thinks that “I’ll achieve that

38
00:02:59,498 --> 00:03:04,518
through consumption, 
acquisition, acquiring

39
00:03:04,518 --> 00:03:07,502
as much of the objective world 
as possible,

40
00:03:07,502 --> 00:03:09,392
and then I’ll find fulfillment.”

41
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:13,032
Just like I’ve mentioned
many times:

42
00:03:13,032 --> 00:03:16,917
through the Internet, 
social networking,

43
00:03:16,917 --> 00:03:25,127
there’re also sites 
you have like matchmaker.com—

44
00:03:25,127 --> 00:03:28,077
that’s one, but there’re many.

45
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:32,068
You smile!
[Laughing]

46
00:03:32,068 --> 00:03:34,749
Where the idea is: 
“Hey!
 

47
00:03:34,749 --> 00:03:40,249
Let’s use all this computing power
to find my soulmate!”

48
00:03:40,259 --> 00:03:42,369
Everyone is searching 
for their counterpart.

49
00:03:42,369 --> 00:03:48,699
What better way then this!
The maximum amount of data.

50
00:03:48,709 --> 00:03:52,509
Like, if we share all the information
that’s known about us

51
00:03:52,509 --> 00:03:55,159
and put that 
in a giant database

52
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:57,181
then there’ll be someone
on the other side—

53
00:03:57,181 --> 00:04:03,531
they put their ideal criteria 
find the match for me.

54
00:04:03,531 --> 00:04:04,531
Like the old song,

55
00:04:04,531 --> 00:04:07,321
“Matchmaker, matchmaker,
make me a match,

56
00:04:07,321 --> 00:04:10,711
find me a find,
catch me a catch.”

57
00:04:10,711 --> 00:04:14,741
Through search,
through the Internet.

58
00:04:14,741 --> 00:04:18,091
It sounds like a good idea,
it sounds tenable.

59
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:23,391
Fill in a form, 
put all my ideal criteria

60
00:04:23,391 --> 00:04:28,863
and then find the match 
in the database.

61
00:04:30,366 --> 00:04:35,013
But then it comes again 
back to

62
00:04:35,013 --> 00:04:38,383
what is our conception of self.

63
00:04:38,383 --> 00:04:42,383
Who are we and 
what are we substantially?

64
00:04:42,673 --> 00:04:47,543
So, if we approach it from 
an exclusively scientific point of view,

65
00:04:47,543 --> 00:04:53,882
then we may conclude that 
we’re carbon–based life forms.

66
00:04:53,882 --> 00:05:03,732
But I can’t imagine someone 
phrasing their search criteria as:

67
00:05:03,732 --> 00:05:09,612
“Carbon–based life form 
seeks intimate relationship

68
00:05:09,612 --> 00:05:13,432
with other carbon–based 
life form.”

69
00:05:13,432 --> 00:05:18,571
Sounds a little … it doesn’t sound
too romantic or appealing.

70
00:05:18,961 --> 00:05:23,791
This seems something less 
than the dignity of the human race.

71
00:05:23,791 --> 00:05:30,988
And less than a full realisation
of our potential.

72
00:05:31,368 --> 00:05:36,761
So, the ideal, 
the search criteria we place,

73
00:05:36,761 --> 00:05:46,781
no matter who we try to impose
this counterpart upon,

74
00:05:46,781 --> 00:05:48,251
the soulmate,

75
00:05:48,251 --> 00:05:52,000
inevitably they disappoint
being less than ideal,

76
00:05:52,000 --> 00:06:00,910
inevitably it becomes frustrated
and enters … dissolves, dissolution.

77
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:06,853
Because no one other than the Absolute
can reciprocate ideal criteria.

78
00:06:06,853 --> 00:06:11,412
Ideal here is synonymous
with the Absolute.

79
00:06:11,412 --> 00:06:14,412
So, indirectly what all this
search is about—

80
00:06:14,412 --> 00:06:18,172
it’s the search for Śrī Kṛṣṇa—
Reality the Beautiful.

